'''The British Stammering Association''' ('''BSA'''), a [[charitable organization|charity]] since 1978, is a national membership organisation in the [[United Kingdom]] for adults and children who [[Stuttering|stammer]], their friends and families, [[Speech-Language Pathology|speech and language therapists]] and other professionals. Based in [[London]], it is run by people who stammer. BSA promotes awareness of stammering, offers advice, information and support to all whose lives are affected by stammering, initiates and supports research into stammering and identifies and promotes effective [[therapy|therapies]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.stammering.org/about_bsa.html|title= About the British Stammering Association|publisher= British Stammering Association|accessdate= 13 April 2012}}</ref> It describes stammering as a [[neurological]] issue<ref name="MPs">{{cite news | url=http://www.politics.co.uk/comment-analysis/2012/12/07/comment-stammering-mps-are-better-than-glib-ones?fb_action_ids=10151355170419882&fb_action_types=og.likes&fb_ref=facebook_referrals&fb_source=timeline_og&action_object_map={%2210151355170419882%22:414496271956581}&action_type_map={%2210151355170419882%22:%22og.likes%22}&action_ref_map={%2210151355170419882%22:%22facebook_referrals%22} | title=Comment: Stammering MPs are better than glib ones | work=politics.co.uk | date=7 December 2012 | accessdate=8 December 2012 | author=Norbert Lieckfeldt}}</ref>and estimates that about 700,000 people in the UK have a stammer.<ref name="MPs"/>

==Organisation==

The Association's Chief Executive is Norbert Lieckfeldt and the Chair is John M Evans.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stammering.org/news_chairmessage2012.html
|title= Message from the new Chair of Trustees |publisher=British Stammering Association|date=September 2012 |accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref>

===Patrons===
In September 2010, the Association announced that Labour front-bench politician [[Ed Balls]], who is now [[Shadow Chancellor of the Exchequer]], had become a [[Patronage#Charity|patron]] of the Association. BSA Chief Executive Norbert Lieckfeldt paid tribute to him for having been very public in his declaration that he too knows what it's like to stammer and has at times struggled with his speech.<ref name="MPs"/><ref>{{cite journal|url= http://stammering.org/edballspatron.html|title=Ed Balls MP becomes BSA patron
|journal=Speaking Out|publisher= British Stammering Association|date=Winter 2010 |accessdate= 15 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/labour/7056823/Ed-Balls-People-who-stammer-avoid-certain-situations-but-in-my-job-you-cant.html|title= Ed Balls: People who stammer avoid certain situations, but in my job you can't |author=Mary Riddell |publisher= ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''| date= 23 January 2010|accessdate=15 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1221870/Ive-battled-stammer-life-reveals-Schools-Secretary-Ed-Balls.html|title= I've battled a stammer all my life, reveals Schools Secretary Ed Balls |publisher= ''[[Daily Mail]]''| date= 21 October 2009|accessdate=15 June 2011}}</ref>

[[David Mitchell (author)|David Mitchell]], author of ''[[Black Swan Green]]'', a [[novel]] about a 13-year-old boy who has a stammer, is also a patron of the Association.<ref>{{cite journal|url= http://stammering.org/bsgrevisited.html|title= Black Swan Green revisited |journal= Speaking Out|publisher= British Stammering Association| date= Spring 2011|accessdate=30 June 2011}}</ref><ref name="Blagger">{{cite news | url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/features/the-blaggers-guide-to-david-mitchell-8498002.html | title=The Blagger's Guide To: David Mitchell | work=[[The Independent on Sunday]] | date=17 February 2013 | accessdate=13 March 2013 | location=London}}</ref>

BSA's other patrons are Sir [[Andrew Bowden]] MBE, Dame [[Margaret Drabble]] DBE,<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2001/oct/20/fiction.books|author= [[Margaret Drabble]]|title= Thankyou and goodnight|publisher= ''[[The Guardian]]''|date=20 October 2001|accessdate= 20 July 2012}}</ref>[[John McAllion]],<ref>{{cite news|url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/3163268.stm|title= Stammerers voice opinions|publisher= ''[[BBC News]]''|date= 4 October 2003|accessdate = 18 July 2012}}</ref> [[Nicholas Parsons]] LL.D. OBE,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.placesandfaces.co.uk/articles/319/a%20-tale-of-the-century.html|title= A Tale of the Century| author= Tony Mallion|publisher=Places&Faces|accessdate= 19 July 2012}}</ref> [[Arwel Richards]],[http://www.arwelrichards.com/#/charity/4572271902/] Jon Smith,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.modcomms.com/interviewdetails.php?inwrId=5|title=Jon Smith|publisher= Modern Communications|accessdate= 23 July 2012}}</ref> and [[Baroness Whitaker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=uzjWRAOzywwC&pg=PA274&lpg=PA274&dq=Baroness+Whitaker+british+stammering+association&source=bl&ots=kebSS3dl1_&sig=PQVThASmHkDo0LgeQHyQSepNrPk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=RxYNUMXEMKaa1AXHsPyoCg&sqi=2&ved=0CGQQ6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=Baroness%20Whitaker%20british%20stammering%20association&f=false|title=Register of Lords' interests: as on 16 July 2004, p.274 |publisher= [[The Stationery Office]] |date= 2004|accessdate= 23 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://stammering.org/about_bsa.html|title= About The British Stammering Association|publisher= British Stammering Association| accessdate=11 October 2011}}</ref>

